<title>USA: Ford sees yen remaining weak.</title>
<headline>Ford sees yen remaining weak.</headline>
<dateline>DEARBORN, Mich. 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ford Motor Co chief financial officer John Devine said Wednesday the automaker expects the Japanese yen, which is at 4-1/2-year lows against the dollar, will continue to be weak.</p>
<p>&quot;Obviously, the yen, we think, is going to stay weak for the foreseeable future,&quot; Devine said in a news conference here.</p>
<p>A weaker yen gives Japanese automakers a pricing advantage in the United States, U.S. automakers contend.</p>
